The paper deals with secret key agreement, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on correlated Gaussian sources, which is a subfield of signal processing and communication (cs.CR, cs.MM). The paper also discusses the trade-off between key generation rate and public communication rate, which is a topic in optimization and control theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with continuous sources, which are commonly encountered in machine learning applications.
